Betafriq, a gaming firm has announced a sponsorship deal with Gor Mahia FC for the next three seasons. The unveiling event has seen Gor Mahia bag a deal worth Sh70 million from the gaming and Entertainment firm Betafriq. Betafriq’s general manager Craig Oyugi distinctively assured all, that the firm will continue investing in Kenyan Sports, with Gor Mahia’s sponsorship being an inception of future involvements. “It’s actually a privilege for Betafriq to be part of a club of such high stature like Gor mahia," said Oyugi. On his part, Ambrose Rachier Gor Mahia’s chairman expressed his gratification noting that Betafriq had come to their rescue at a time when the club had no sponsor. “I want to assure our sponsors that we are going to give in our best and go back to where we belong by the end of the season. The gaming firm was among the first companies to have their license renewed by BCLB.